# Farhana

Actuary. Expert interviewee featured in [[entities/Schola]]'s job guide for the [[concepts/Actuary-Career]].

## Insights (from Schola interview)

**On daily work:**
- Role involves heavy use of Excel and some coding
- Applies maths, statistics, and financial theory to predict risks and advise companies

**On becoming an actuary:**
- Start in entry-level roles after completing a degree
- Pass professional exams (IFoA or SOA) over 3–7 years while working
- An Actuarial Science degree is not strictly required; any degree is viable if professional exams are passed
- Actuarial Science graduates may receive exam exemptions

**On exams:**
- Actuarial exams are required for certification and significantly improve career prospects

**On demand:**
- High demand in insurance companies and consulting firms
- Global opportunities open up, especially after gaining experience and certification
